    \FirstLetter{O} give the Lord, you s\pointup{o}ns of God,\Med\\
    give the Lord glory \pointup{a}nd power;\\
give the Lord the glory \pointup{o}f his name.\Med\\
    Adore the Lord in his hol\pointup{y} court.

The Lord’s voice resounding \pointup{o}n the waters,\Med\\
    the Lord on the immensity \pointup{o}f waters;\\
the voice of the Lord, f\pointup{u}ll of power,\Med\\
    the voice of the Lord, full \pointup{o}f splendour.

The Lord’s voice shatter\pointup{\i}ng the cedars,\Med\\
    the Lord shatters the cedars \pointup{o}f Lebanon;\\
he makes Lebanon leap l\pointup{\i}ke a calf\Med\\
    and Sirion like a young w\pointup{\i}ld ox.

The Lord’s voice flashes flames of f\pointup{\i}re.\Flex\\
    The Lord’s voice shak\pointup{\i}ng the wilderness,\Med\\
    the Lord shakes the wilderness \pointup{o}f Kadesh;\\
the Lord’s voice rend\pointup{\i}ng the oak tree\Med\\
    and stripping the for\pointup{e}st bare.

The God of gl\pointup{o}ry thunders.\Med\\
    In his temple they all cr\pointup{y}: ‘Glory!’\\
The Lord sat enthroned ov\pointup{e}r the flood;\Med\\
    the Lord sits as king f\pointup{o}r ever.

The Lord will give strength t\pointup{o} his people,\Med\\
    the Lord will bless his people w\pointup{\i}th peace.

Glory to the Father and t\pointup{o} the Son,\Med\\
    and to the Hol\pointup{y} Spirit:\\
as it was in the beginn\pointup{\i}ng, is now,\Med\\
    and will be for ever. \pointupl{A}men.
